The DJIA performed the worst  falling nearly 100 points  while the S&P 500 and Nasdaq registered some gains  breaking away from the 2-day losing streak.There were some key corporate news  and let's dive into that.ðŸŽ¯Apple is said to stop its car project ambition as it pivots towards generative AI as the next phase of growth. Despite the announcement  we did not see major movement in major automobile stocks. Rumours have pressured legacy car markets since the news of a potential Apple car has been looming in the industry for a long time. The initial plan was thought to be a transformative Apple EV car that could transform into a self-driving vehicle.Shares of Beyond Meat rose sharply after hours  flipping a multi-bagger at one time as the company announced a robust fourth-quarter result where revenue was up more than expected despite a widening loss.The rosy revenue growth comes from its international market  which saw retail sales jump 22% and restaurant sales climb 34% by introducing new exciting product lines in an environment boosted by firm sales at key European fast-food chains.ðŸŽ¯Beyond the result  there has always been some scepticism about the potential health and environmental goodness of such plant-based meats  which could sway public opinions and affect outlook too.ðŸ’°What's on the menu today?ðŸ’°At 9.30 pm  we will have a key piece of economic data: GDP and other related consumer spending data.FOMC member Bostic will also speak at 1 am  and Williams will speak at 1.45 am. The market has been challenging  and with major key data released  our hedge has been declining in value  which affects returns.
